WEBVTT

00:09.310 --> 00:12.646
PREVIOUSLY ON
"UNITED STATES OF TARA"...

00:12.680 --> 00:14.348
MAX, I REALLY APPRECIATE
HOW WELCOMING YOU'VE BEEN.

00:14.382 --> 00:16.217
I KNOW
NEIL'S YOUR BUDDY.

00:16.250 --> 00:18.419
WELL, YOU'RE A STAND-UP GUY,
NICK, RAISING ANOTHER GUY'S KID.

00:18.452 --> 00:19.620
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO HUSTLE OUT OF HERE.

00:19.653 --> 00:21.189
NEIL'S ABOUT TO STOP BY.

00:21.222 --> 00:22.456
HE KNOWS ABOUT THE WEDDING
BEING TOMORROW?

00:22.490 --> 00:23.724
I CAME TO SAY GOODBYE.
"GOODBYE"?

00:23.757 --> 00:25.326
WITH CHARMAINE
GETTING MARRIED,

00:25.359 --> 00:27.461
THERE'S NOTHING LEFT FOR ME
HERE, LIFEWISE.

00:27.495 --> 00:29.063
I NEED TO GET YOU
OUT OF THIS HOUSE.

00:29.097 --> 00:30.598
IT'S REALLY
NOT THAT BAD.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.800
I WANT YOU TO START LOOKING
IN THE PAPER AT CONDOS.

00:32.833 --> 00:34.468
MAYBE IT IS THAT BAD.

00:34.502 --> 00:37.205
LIONEL REALLY HEARTS ME.
WE MADE OUT.

00:37.238 --> 00:39.173
WHO IS MIMI?

00:39.207 --> 00:40.674
MAYBE A BABYSITTER.

00:40.708 --> 00:43.577
I WASN'T YOUR BABYSITTER.
I RUN A FOSTER HOME.

00:43.611 --> 00:46.547
[ As Chicken ]
I DON'T WANT TO RIDE A TRICYCLE.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.816
OH, MY GOD.
IT'S...CHICKEN.

00:48.849 --> 00:51.319
CHICKEN WAS TARA'S NICKNAME
WHEN WE WERE LITTLE KIDS.

00:51.352 --> 00:53.821
PROMISE ME
NOT ONE WORD

00:53.854 --> 00:56.357
TO MOM AND DAD
TILL MONDAY MORNING,

00:56.390 --> 01:01.229
WHILE I AM DEALING NICK
HIS BRIDAL-SUITE BLOWJOB.

01:11.739 --> 01:14.775
* OPEN UP THE SKY

01:14.808 --> 01:18.346
* THIS MESS IS GETTING HIGH

01:18.379 --> 01:23.284
* IT'S WINDY,
AND OUR FAMILY NEEDS A RIDE *

01:25.386 --> 01:30.191
* I KNOW WE'LL BE JUST FINE

01:30.224 --> 01:35.563
* WHEN WE LEARN
TO LOVE THE RIDE *

01:36.764 --> 01:41.635
* I KNOW WE'LL BE FINE

01:41.669 --> 01:48.642
* WHEN WE LEARN
TO LOVE THE RIDE *

01:48.676 --> 01:53.281
* I KNOW WE'LL BE JUST FINE

01:53.314 --> 01:57.651
* WHEN WE LEARN
TO LOVE THE RIDE *

02:05.259 --> 02:08.762
OH, MY GOD!
IT'S ALL HAPPENING!

02:08.796 --> 02:10.498
MAX, YOU DID IT!

02:10.531 --> 02:12.366
SOMETIMES
I DO ALL RIGHT.

02:12.400 --> 02:16.570
I MEAN, IT IS SERIOUSLY
EVERYTHING I DREAMED OF.

02:16.604 --> 02:19.907
YEP. AND MOM AND DAD ARE
GONNA SHOW UP ANY MINUTE NOW.

02:19.940 --> 02:21.642
I WANT THEM
AT MY WEDDING.

02:21.675 --> 02:23.544
AND MOM'S
GONNA DO THAT THING

02:23.577 --> 02:25.646
WHERE SHE HOLDS HER ARMS OPEN
LIKE SHE'S A WARM PERSON.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.315
MAX,
COULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR

02:27.348 --> 02:29.550
AND HOT-GLUE-GUN HER LIPS
TOGETHER FOR ME, PLEASE?

02:29.583 --> 02:31.585
AND YOU'RE GONNA LET A MAN
WHO BASICALLY GAVE US AWAY

02:31.619 --> 02:32.720
GIVE YOU AWAY.

02:32.753 --> 02:34.522
YOU KNOW WHAT?

02:34.555 --> 02:35.723
IT'S JUST A SYMBOL, OKAY?

02:35.756 --> 02:37.458
IT DOESN'T MEAN ANYTHING
TO ME.

02:37.491 --> 02:38.792
OH, IT DOESN'T MEAN
ANYTHING TO YOU

02:38.826 --> 02:41.262
THAT WE WERE
IN MOTHERFUCKING FOSTER CARE?

02:41.295 --> 02:43.264
I JUST FEEL LIKE UNTIL
WE GET THE TRUTH OUT OF THEM --

02:43.297 --> 02:45.333
WE GOT THE TRUTH.
WE LIVED AT MIMI'S.

02:45.366 --> 02:47.201
UH, YOU'RE FORGETTING
THE BIGGER QUESTION, CHAR --

02:47.235 --> 02:48.936
WHAT WERE WE DOING THERE
IN THE FIRST PLACE?

02:48.969 --> 02:50.338
I DON'T KNOW, TARA.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

02:50.371 --> 02:51.872
MAYBE TODAY --

02:51.905 --> 02:56.410
MAYBE TODAY I DON'T REALLY CARE
ABOUT ANY OF THAT.

02:56.444 --> 02:59.380
WELL, MAYBE TODAY
I DON'T WANT TO SEE MOM AND DAD.

03:00.514 --> 03:02.550
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

03:02.583 --> 03:03.984
PLEASE, LADY,

03:04.017 --> 03:07.421
JUST PUT ON A SIMPLE FROCK
AND SIT THERE, OKAY?

03:07.455 --> 03:08.956
YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE
TO SMILE.
GOOD,
'CAUSE I DON'T WANT TO.

03:08.989 --> 03:10.958
GOOD! DON'T!

03:10.991 --> 03:13.661
OH, GOD!

03:16.264 --> 03:17.831
YOU SEE MY POINT,
RIGHT?

03:17.865 --> 03:19.333
OH, YEAH.

03:19.367 --> 03:21.835
DON'T SAY
YOU ALSO SEE HERS.

03:21.869 --> 03:24.872
I'M ONLY LOOKING
AT YOURS.

03:27.541 --> 03:29.877
[ BOTH EXHALING LOUDLY ]

03:32.646 --> 03:35.316
FEELING A LITTLE FAINT.
I JUST GRAYED OUT.

03:35.349 --> 03:37.285
KEEP BLOWING.

03:37.318 --> 03:39.453
YOU KNOW, I THINK IT'S NICE
TO RESET THE MEMORY

03:39.487 --> 03:41.589
OF BLOWING UP BALLOONS
AS SOMETHING LESS SKEEZY,

03:41.622 --> 03:42.756
LIKE LOVE.

03:42.790 --> 03:44.458
[ Sarcastically ]
LOVE.

03:44.492 --> 03:47.561
YOU REFER TO YOUR
BALLOON-CENTERED
PROSTITUTION EMPIRE?

03:47.595 --> 03:49.297
THAT WAS NOT
PROSTITUTION.

03:49.330 --> 03:51.965
I NEVER SHOWED ANYONE
MY BOOBS OR MY GINEY.

03:51.999 --> 03:53.434
"GINEY."

03:53.467 --> 03:56.504
OPRAH RUINED
"VA-JAY-JAY."

03:56.537 --> 03:59.607
PEOPLE BOUGHT YOU STUFF
SO THEY COULD BOSS YOU AROUND.

03:59.640 --> 04:01.008
IF THAT WAS
PROSTITUTION,

04:01.041 --> 04:02.910
THEN EVERY WIFE ON THIS STREET
WOULD BE A HOOKER,

04:02.943 --> 04:04.512
PLUS THE STAY-AT-HOME DAD

04:04.545 --> 04:06.347
WHO'S MARRIED
TO THE LADY CHIROPRACTOR.

04:06.380 --> 04:09.350
WHAT DOES THAT SAY
ABOUT ZACH GETTING YOU A CONDO?

04:09.383 --> 04:12.019
HEY, MOOSH, GOT TO DO
WHAT'S RIGHT FOR ME.

04:12.052 --> 04:14.888
I GOT TO START
MY OWN LIFE.

04:14.922 --> 04:16.757
[ POP ]
AAH!

04:16.790 --> 04:17.925
[ SIGHS ]

04:19.993 --> 04:21.295
[ SIGHS ]

04:21.329 --> 04:22.830
HEY,
ANY SIGHT OF THEM YET?

04:22.863 --> 04:24.632
NO.

04:24.665 --> 04:27.501
BECAUSE I HEAR DOGS HOWLING
IN THE SURROUNDING BLOCKS.

04:27.535 --> 04:29.303
I WANT TO HIDE.

04:29.337 --> 04:30.971
JUST DO IT.
I WON'T TELL.

04:31.004 --> 04:34.508
POP OUT THE LAST MINUTE,
WATCH THE THING, THEN BAIL.

04:34.542 --> 04:35.943
HERE THEY COME.

04:35.976 --> 04:37.511
WHERE YOU GONNA HIDE?

04:37.545 --> 04:39.012
NOWHERE, I GUESS.

04:39.046 --> 04:40.548
MAYBE RIGHT HERE,
BEHIND MY FACE.

04:40.581 --> 04:41.982
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:42.015 --> 04:43.917
HEY, LOOK AT THAT --
YOUR MOM'S DRIVING.

04:43.951 --> 04:46.620
HUH. THAT'S WEIRD.
DAD NEVER LETS HER DRIVE.

04:46.654 --> 04:49.690
PREPARE YOURSELF FOR THE WORLD'S
BULLSHITTIEST HELLO.

04:49.723 --> 04:51.325
HI!

04:51.359 --> 04:52.660
HI!

04:52.693 --> 04:55.896
Max: HEY,
WHAT TOOK YOU GUYS SO LONG?

04:55.929 --> 04:59.333
HEY, MAX, YOU EVER HEARD
OF THE GRUNION RUN?

04:59.367 --> 05:00.734
GRUNION RUN? NO.

05:00.768 --> 05:03.371
YOUR FATHER'S
DISCOVERED THE INTERNET.

05:03.404 --> 05:05.072
HE WANTS TO GO
TO CALIFORNIA.

05:05.105 --> 05:06.540
GET THE GIFT, FRANK.

05:06.574 --> 05:08.075
SAN LUIS OBISPO.

05:08.108 --> 05:11.445
APPARENTLY, PEOPLE GO OUT
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

05:11.479 --> 05:12.946
AND GRAB THEM
WITH THEIR BARE HANDS.

05:12.980 --> 05:14.948
GRAB THEM
WITH THEIR BARE HANDS.

05:14.982 --> 05:17.851
FRANK, THE GIFT.

05:17.885 --> 05:20.954
I JUST HAD A LONG TALK
WITH HIS DOCTOR.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.490
I'LL FILL YOU IN LATER.

05:25.593 --> 05:27.428
Kate: BYE-BYE,
FROGGY ALARM CLOCK.

05:27.461 --> 05:29.363
THERE IS NO LILY PAD FOR YOU

05:29.397 --> 05:31.832
AT MY NEW
TOP-FLOOR PENTHOUSE SUITE.

05:31.865 --> 05:33.834
I LOVE THE WAY THAT SOUNDS.

05:33.867 --> 05:36.103
[ Haughtily ] "TOP-FLOOR
PENTHOUSE SUITE, PLEASE."

05:36.136 --> 05:38.038
WHO ARE YOU
TALKING TO?

05:38.071 --> 05:39.139
[ Normal voice ] YOU.

05:39.172 --> 05:40.841
WE'RE IN THE ELEVATOR,

05:40.874 --> 05:43.444
AND YOU'RE PRESSING THE BUTTON
SO I CAN WATCH IT GLOW.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.112
"TOP FLOOR" AND "PENTHOUSE"
ARE REDUNDANT.

05:45.145 --> 05:46.947
"PENTHOUSE"
MEANS "TOP FLOOR."

05:46.980 --> 05:48.549
MM.

05:48.582 --> 05:50.784
THAT IS ONE OF THE MANY THINGS
YOU CAN TEACH ME

05:50.818 --> 05:52.085
WHEN YOU VISIT ME
AT MY OWN PLACE!

05:52.119 --> 05:53.454
[ TOY SQUEAKS ]

05:53.487 --> 05:54.922
OH, I WILL DO MORE
THAN VISIT.

05:54.955 --> 05:57.391
WE CAN EAT DINNER
TOGETHER...

05:57.425 --> 05:58.859
MAKE BUBBLE BATHS...

05:58.892 --> 06:01.629
SIT ON WHITE FURNITURE
NAKED.

06:03.897 --> 06:04.865
HEY, KATE,
DO YOU WANT TO --

06:04.898 --> 06:06.767
[ TOY SQUEAKS ]

06:06.800 --> 06:08.602
HI, DAD.

06:08.636 --> 06:10.504
THIS IS ZACH.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.041
ZACH.

06:14.074 --> 06:16.009
PLEASURE.

06:16.043 --> 06:18.011
WHAT, UH...
WHAT'S IN THE BOX?

06:18.045 --> 06:19.880
THIS?

06:19.913 --> 06:21.782
OH,
THIS IS FOR GOODWILL.

06:21.815 --> 06:24.051
JUST PARING DOWN
TO A FEW ESSENTIALS, YOU KNOW.

06:24.084 --> 06:25.853
I'M GREEN LIKE 'DAT.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.058
OKAY. THAT'S GOOD.

06:31.091 --> 06:33.494
OKAY.

06:33.527 --> 06:35.729
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

06:35.763 --> 06:36.830
OKAY.

06:40.200 --> 06:41.134
[ SCOFFS ]

06:43.804 --> 06:46.073
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA
TELL THEM?

06:46.106 --> 06:48.008
RIGHT AS I'M LEAVING.

06:48.041 --> 06:49.610
KIND OF LIKE,

06:49.643 --> 06:53.981
"HEY, FAMILY,
I'M JUST NOT THAT INTO YOU!"

06:54.014 --> 06:55.749
I WISH I DIDN'T HAVE TO BOYCOTT
THE WEDDING TODAY,

06:55.783 --> 06:57.718
BUT IT'S UNFAIR,
MARSHALL.

06:57.751 --> 06:59.453
BREEDERS TAKE EVERYTHING
FOR GRANTED --

06:59.487 --> 07:01.054
MARRIAGE, BABIES...

07:01.088 --> 07:02.189
LEGGINGS.

07:02.222 --> 07:03.657
YOU COULD WEAR LEGGINGS.

07:03.691 --> 07:05.493
YOU WORE LEGGINGS
IN "MACBETH."

07:05.526 --> 07:08.028
THE SCOTTISH PLAY?

07:08.061 --> 07:10.564
IT'S ONLY UNLUCKY
TO SAY IT IN A THEATER.

07:10.598 --> 07:12.099
MACBETH! MACBETH!

07:12.132 --> 07:14.101
OKAY, ANY STRAIGHT PERSON
WHO GETS MARRIED

07:14.134 --> 07:16.804
WHILE THE COUNTRY STILL
CONSIDERS GAY MARRIAGE ILLEGAL

07:16.837 --> 07:19.072
IS BASICALLY
A HOLOCAUST DENIER.

07:19.106 --> 07:21.542
HMM. THAT SEEMS
A BIT OF A STRETCH.

07:21.575 --> 07:23.611
A PERSON
WHO STANDS FOR NOTHING

07:23.644 --> 07:25.212
SPENDS THEIR WHOLE LIFE
SITTING.

07:25.245 --> 07:28.882
WELL, JUST SO YOU KNOW,
I'M TIRED.

07:28.916 --> 07:30.818
I NEED TO SIT DOWN
SOMETIMES.

07:30.851 --> 07:33.854
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
TO BE TIRED ABOUT, BOY?

07:33.887 --> 07:36.256
MY MOM WENT ON A TRIP
TO MEET HER MOLESTER,

07:36.289 --> 07:38.726
AND I DIDN'T EVEN GET
A LOUSY T-SHIRT.

07:41.128 --> 07:42.530
I WANT
TO HUG IT BETTER.

07:44.264 --> 07:46.767
CAN I HUG YOU?

07:52.806 --> 07:56.209
PLEASE JUST COME TO THE WEDDING
AND SIT NEXT TO ME.

07:57.611 --> 07:59.580
OKAY.

07:59.613 --> 08:02.750
I'LL COME
TO THE WEDDING.

08:02.783 --> 08:05.152
WITHOUT SIGNS
OR BULLHORNS

08:05.185 --> 08:07.821
OR ANYTHING
CLOSE TO A PROTEST.

08:07.855 --> 08:11.725
I WILL KEEP
MY BIG, FAT, GAY MOUTH SHUT.

08:11.759 --> 08:13.026
FOR YOU.

08:13.060 --> 08:14.828
THANK YOU.

08:16.730 --> 08:20.701
BIG...FAT...
GAY...MOUTH.

08:27.841 --> 08:29.543
MIMI:
You've reached the Parmeters.

08:29.577 --> 08:31.011
Can't take your call right now,

08:31.044 --> 08:33.747
so go ahead
and leave a brief message.

08:33.781 --> 08:34.915
[ Beep ]

08:34.948 --> 08:36.950
HI, THIS IS TARA -- GREGSON.

08:36.984 --> 08:41.288
I'M, UH, I'M CALLING
TO APOLOGIZE FOR...

08:41.321 --> 08:44.825
WELL, DURING OUR VISIT,
I KNOW I WAS INAPPROPRIATE,

08:44.858 --> 08:46.594
AND, UH...

08:46.627 --> 08:49.096
BUT I-I-I HAVE
SO MANY QUESTIONS,

08:49.129 --> 08:51.031
AND I WAS REALLY HOPING --

08:51.064 --> 08:53.634
DAD, WHAT ARE YOU --
GOD, I COULD HAVE BEEN --

08:53.667 --> 08:55.936
DID YOU KNOW THAT ALSO
IN SAN LUIS OF PISMO,

08:55.969 --> 08:58.138
THERE'S THIS PLACE
CALLED BUBBLE GUM ALLEY?

08:58.171 --> 09:00.641
A WHOLE WALL MADE UP
OF CHEWED-UP CHEWING GUM.

09:00.674 --> 09:02.943
I MEAN, IF YOU HAVE --
IF YOU HAVE A COMPUTER,

09:02.976 --> 09:04.945
WE COULD GOOGLE IT
TOGETHER.

09:04.978 --> 09:08.148
WELL, I'M -- I'M GETTING READY
FOR THE WEDDING.

09:08.181 --> 09:11.619
IS THERE SOMETHING
YOU NEED, DAD?

09:11.652 --> 09:13.787
OH, GOD.

09:13.821 --> 09:16.189
OH, IT'S ALL, UH...

09:16.223 --> 09:20.060
IT'S ALL, UH...

09:20.093 --> 09:22.195
I'VE MADE
SO MANY MISTAKES.

09:22.229 --> 09:27.067
TOO MANY MISTAKES.

09:27.100 --> 09:28.936
I WISH YOU GIRLS COULD HAVE HAD
YOUR BROTHER HERE

09:28.969 --> 09:31.739
FOR CHARMAINE'S
GRADUATION.

09:31.772 --> 09:33.941
WELL,
THIS IS CHARMAINE'S WEDDING.

09:33.974 --> 09:35.943
CHARMAINE NEVER GRADUATED
FROM ANYTHING.

09:35.976 --> 09:38.679
AND WE DON'T HAVE
A BROTHER.

09:38.712 --> 09:40.914
FROM MY FIRST MARRIAGE.

09:43.050 --> 09:45.018
BUT HE WASN'T WELL.

09:45.052 --> 09:46.987
YOU AREN'T WELL.

09:47.020 --> 09:49.923
MUST BE MY SPERM.

09:49.957 --> 09:52.826
EH, TWO OUT OF THREE.
WHO KNOWS?

09:52.860 --> 09:55.629
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT, DAD?

09:57.798 --> 10:00.300
OOH.
GAY BOYS IN LOVE.

10:00.333 --> 10:01.802
OOH.
STRAIGHT PEOPLE IN LOVE.

10:03.270 --> 10:04.237
HEY, TED.

10:04.271 --> 10:05.839
FELICITATIONS.

10:05.873 --> 10:08.041
I'D LAY OFF THE COCK-SMOKING
TONIGHT, BOYS.

10:09.409 --> 10:10.844
ASPARAGUS?

10:10.878 --> 10:13.046
EH, DON'T LET HER
SCARE YOU.

10:13.080 --> 10:15.082
A FEW SPEARS OF FRESH PINEAPPLE
CLEARS IT UP.

10:15.115 --> 10:16.784
TAKE IT FROM ME.

10:16.817 --> 10:20.020
NOW, I'VE GOT
IVORIES TO TICKLE.

10:22.422 --> 10:26.226
OH, ZACH,
THIS IS MY BROTHER'S...

10:29.362 --> 10:30.898
...BOYFRIEND.

10:30.931 --> 10:32.700
NICE MEETING YOU.

10:32.733 --> 10:34.134
MAKING FOOD
FOR THE HAPPY EVENT?

10:34.167 --> 10:36.269
OH,
HAPPY FOR SOME PEOPLE.

10:36.303 --> 10:38.438
HARDER FOR OTHERS TO ENJOY
WHEN THIS COUNTRY --

10:38.471 --> 10:39.907
LIONEL, PLEASE.

10:39.940 --> 10:42.409
NO, NO, LET HIM --
LET HIM FINISH.

10:42.442 --> 10:43.777
NOTHING. I JUST...

10:43.811 --> 10:45.378
I JUST THINK THAT OBAMA

10:45.412 --> 10:47.447
LED THE GAY AND LESBIAN
COMMUNITY ASTRAY, THAT'S ALL.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.049
HMM.

10:49.082 --> 10:50.984
[ Chuckling ]
I'M NOT SURE ABOUT THAT.

10:51.018 --> 10:55.288
NOT THAT
I VOTED FOR HIM.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.323
WHAT?

10:56.356 --> 10:57.691
YOU'RE A REPUBLICAN?

10:57.725 --> 11:00.027
I LIKED RON PAUL.

11:00.060 --> 11:01.695
BUT MY REAL PROBLEM
IS WITH THE WAY

11:01.729 --> 11:03.363
THE GAY COMMUNITY
IS ATTEMPTING TO BE HEARD.

11:03.396 --> 11:04.998
JUST TELL ME SOMETHING

11:05.032 --> 11:08.368
THAT NO ONE ON YOUR SIDE
SEEMS WILLING TO ADMIT TO.

11:08.401 --> 11:11.438
DEEP INSIDE,
YOU ACTUALLY BELIEVE

11:11.471 --> 11:13.741
THAT MARRIAGE
IS FOR PUSSIES AND DICKS.

11:16.309 --> 11:19.346
WELL, I GUESS
I'D HAVE TO SAY YES.

11:19.379 --> 11:21.081
[ SCOFFS ]

11:21.114 --> 11:22.883
I'M OUT, MARSH.

11:22.916 --> 11:25.418
SEXT ME
WHEN THE WEDDING IS OVER.

11:28.488 --> 11:32.793
WOW. WELL,
LIONEL'S IN QUITE A MOOD.

11:32.826 --> 11:35.729
RON PAUL? REALLY?

11:41.101 --> 11:42.770
DON'T TOUCH!

11:42.803 --> 11:44.304
I JUST PUT ON
MY BODY BLING.

11:44.337 --> 11:47.140
PEOPLE EXPECT ME TO HAVE
SOME STUPID PREGNANT GLOW.

11:47.174 --> 11:48.508
DAD JUST SAID
THE MOST FUCKED-UP THING.

11:48.541 --> 11:50.143
YEAH, YEAH.

11:50.177 --> 11:52.145
DAD HATES INDIANS -- WHATEVER.
DAD'S CRAZY.

11:52.179 --> 11:54.047
NO, NO, I WAS IN THE BATHROOM,
AND DAD CAME IN,

11:54.081 --> 11:56.149
AND, OKAY, HE DIDN'T EXACTLY
MAKE THAT MUCH SENSE,

11:56.183 --> 11:58.285
BUT HE TOLD ME
WE HAVE A BROTHER.

11:58.318 --> 12:00.387
A BROTHER?
COME ON.

12:00.420 --> 12:01.889
YES!

12:01.922 --> 12:03.957
I MEAN, HE SAID IT
IN A TOTALLY DISJOINTED,

12:03.991 --> 12:05.759
EARLY ALZHEIMER'S,
DAD-LIKE WAY,

12:05.793 --> 12:08.495
BUT HE SAID, "YOU AND YOUR
SISTER HAVE A HALF BROTHER.

12:08.528 --> 12:11.464
AND I WAS MARRIED
BEFORE I MET YOUR MOM."

12:11.498 --> 12:14.001
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, LET'S SEE.

12:14.034 --> 12:17.304
DAD ALSO THINKS
THAT BOB HOPE'S STILL ALIVE,

12:17.337 --> 12:19.306
THAT KATE'S NAME
IS PATRICIA,

12:19.339 --> 12:20.874
AND THAT I'M STILL
IN COMMUNITY COLLEGE.

12:20.908 --> 12:22.209
DON'T YOU THINK
HE'S A LITTLE CONFUSED?

12:22.242 --> 12:25.345
OR MAYBE
HE'S HAVING A LUCID MOMENT.

12:25.378 --> 12:27.214
TARA...

12:27.247 --> 12:30.250
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT TODAY IS?

12:30.283 --> 12:31.484
[ SIGHS ]

12:31.518 --> 12:35.789
TODAY IS MY BULLET TRAIN
TO A NEW LIFE.

12:35.823 --> 12:38.859
NICK SAILS, TARA.

12:38.892 --> 12:41.228
I MEAN,
THEY HAVE A SAILBOAT.

12:42.930 --> 12:44.998
THEY'RE NORMAL PEOPLE.

12:45.032 --> 12:48.301
AND THEY'RE MAKING ROOM

12:48.335 --> 12:53.240
IN THEIR NORMAL-PEOPLE
GROUP PHOTOS...

12:53.273 --> 12:55.475
...FOR ME.

12:55.508 --> 12:58.545
IF MY BODY
DOESN'T BLING,

12:58.578 --> 13:03.016
IF OUR DAD DOESN'T
WALK ME DOWN THE AISLE,

13:03.050 --> 13:08.255
IF MY SISTER DITCHES -- OKAY? --
AT THE LAST SECOND,

13:08.288 --> 13:12.225
THEN THESE NORMAL PEOPLE
WILL KNOW...

13:12.259 --> 13:14.594
THAT THERE IS
SOMETHING WRONG WITH ME.

13:14.627 --> 13:16.096
OH...

13:16.129 --> 13:20.333
AND I WILL NEVER
GET THE FUCK OUT.

13:27.107 --> 13:29.009
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

13:33.313 --> 13:35.916
[ As Chicken ] I WANT TO COME
TO YOUR WEDDING, CHAR-CHAR.

13:35.949 --> 13:38.451
CAN I BE
YOUR FLOWER GIRL?

13:38.485 --> 13:42.489
OH!

13:42.522 --> 13:44.892
[ PIANO PLAYS SOFTLY ]

13:49.362 --> 13:52.933
MY GOD. YOU'VE GOT
SUCH A BEAUTIFUL LONG NECK.

13:52.966 --> 13:55.068
LIKE A MODIGLIANI.

13:55.102 --> 13:57.070
I GET THAT CONSTANTLY.

13:59.439 --> 14:01.108
WOW.

14:01.141 --> 14:03.510
OKAY, CAN YOU DO THAT HARDER
OR NOT AT ALL?

14:03.543 --> 14:05.478
IT'S LIKE THERE'S A RADIO
IN THE OTHER ROOM,

14:05.512 --> 14:07.380
BUT I CAN ONLY HEAR IT ENOUGH
TO GO CRAZY.

14:07.414 --> 14:10.450
YOU'RE STRESSED BEING HERE
AMONG ALL THIS, HUH, SWEETIE?

14:10.483 --> 14:13.620
YEAH, WELL, WEDDINGS BLOW,
AS A RULE OF THUMB.

14:13.653 --> 14:15.155
IT'LL BE WONDERFUL
TO SEE YOU

14:15.188 --> 14:17.357
FINALLY GET
SOME OF YOUR BOUNDARIES UP,

14:17.390 --> 14:19.092
GET AWAY FROM HERE.

14:19.126 --> 14:22.662
I DON'T THINK I NEED
TO GET AWAY FROM HERE, PER SE.

14:22.695 --> 14:27.935
I'M JUST OVER THIS HOUSE
AND ITS LACK OF POOL, GYM,

14:27.968 --> 14:30.037
WHITE-AND-GRAY
MARBLE COUNTERTOPS.

14:30.070 --> 14:32.172
WELL, WE'RE NOT GETTING
YOU YOUR OWN PLACE
FOR THE AMENITIES.

14:32.205 --> 14:34.141
I WANT TO PROTECT YOU.

14:34.174 --> 14:36.176
I DON'T NEED
PROTECTION.

14:36.209 --> 14:38.245
YOU LIVE
WITH SICK PEOPLE.

14:38.278 --> 14:40.513
SICK PERSON.
AND I LOVE HER.

14:40.547 --> 14:42.382
OF COURSE YOU WANT
TO COVER FOR HER.

14:42.415 --> 14:45.285
THAT'S NATURAL
IN AN ABUSE SITUATION.

14:45.318 --> 14:47.254
BUT YOUR INSTINCTS
ARE OFF.

14:47.287 --> 14:48.555
MY INSTINCTS?

14:48.588 --> 14:50.090
I AM NOT THE ONE
COMPARING WOMEN

14:50.123 --> 14:51.925
TO MASSIVELY DISTORTED
MODERN PAINTINGS.

14:51.959 --> 14:53.927
KATE, I'M --
AND THE OTHER THING
THAT BOTHERED ME

14:53.961 --> 14:55.362
IS YOU BASICALLY IMPLIED

14:55.395 --> 14:57.464
THAT MY BROTHER ISN'T
GOOD ENOUGH TO GET MARRIED.

14:57.497 --> 15:00.233
AND YOU KEEP
CALLING MY MOM CRAZY.

15:00.267 --> 15:02.202
I AM THE ONLY ONE
THAT CAN CALL MY MOM CRAZY.

15:04.304 --> 15:05.538
YOU KNOW WHAT?

15:05.572 --> 15:07.540
I THINK THAT I WOULD LIKE
TO SPEND SOME TIME

15:07.574 --> 15:09.309
WITH MY FUCKED-UP FAMILY
ALONE.

15:09.342 --> 15:11.011
SORRY, DUDE.

15:11.044 --> 15:13.680
THIS IS JUST NOT THE PLACE
FOR A NORMAL GUY, LIKE YOU.

15:13.713 --> 15:15.148
KATE, I THINK
YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

15:15.182 --> 15:17.017
KATE!
THAT SURE HAPPENED FAST.

15:17.050 --> 15:18.418
JUST GIVE ME ONE SECOND,
NAY NAY.

15:18.451 --> 15:20.020
OKAY, FELLA,
OFF YOU GO.

15:20.053 --> 15:21.454
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

15:21.488 --> 15:24.291
I DON'T, EITHER.

15:24.324 --> 15:25.425
OR THE --
OR THE FISH.

15:25.458 --> 15:27.294
CHICKEN!
SO IF YOU COULD --

15:27.327 --> 15:28.661
TARA, STOP IT.

15:28.695 --> 15:30.563
I-I'LL BE WITH YOU
IN -- IN A MINUTE.

15:30.597 --> 15:32.499
CHAR, I-I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
RIGHT NOW.

15:32.532 --> 15:34.334
NOT NOW, NICK.
TARA NEEDS ME.

15:34.367 --> 15:36.970
IF YOU COULD JUST GIVE ME
ONE MINUTE, CHARMAINE.

15:37.004 --> 15:39.039
PLEASE,
LOOK, I NEED YOU

15:39.072 --> 15:40.607
TO BE STRONG ENOUGH
TO BE MY MAN, OKAY?

15:40.640 --> 15:42.375
JUST LIKE
OUR SONG SAYS.

15:42.409 --> 15:44.411
YOU NEED TO DO SOMETHING
ABOUT HER.

15:44.444 --> 15:46.579
I WOULD
IF YOU WOULD LET GO OF MY ARM.

15:46.613 --> 15:49.983
NICK, YOUR FINGERS
ARE DIGGING INTO MY SKIN.

15:50.017 --> 15:52.185
I MEAN, JESUS, HOW MUCH
AM I SUPPOSED TO PUT UP WITH?

15:52.219 --> 15:54.321
I ALREADY AGREED
TO RAISE YOUR BABY.

15:54.354 --> 15:56.356
[ HUMMING ]

16:03.530 --> 16:06.499
[ PIANO PLAYS PACHELBEL'S
"CANON IN D MAJOR" ]

16:08.368 --> 16:10.303
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

16:12.439 --> 16:15.475
[ GUESTS MURMURING ]

16:15.508 --> 16:17.010
OH, JUST PLAY ALONG,
EVERYBODY.

16:17.044 --> 16:18.278
IT'S FUNNY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:18.311 --> 16:19.546
IT'S FOR YouTube.

16:31.691 --> 16:35.795
[ SIGHS ] YOU'VE MADE ME
SO HAPPY, SWEETIE.

16:35.828 --> 16:38.398
THANK YOU
FOR MARRYING ME.

16:38.431 --> 16:41.234
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

16:41.268 --> 16:43.670
LET'S PLOW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:53.713 --> 16:54.747
COME HERE, HONEY.

16:57.450 --> 17:00.587
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

17:00.620 --> 17:04.457
GOOD AFTERNOON,
FRIENDS, LOVED ONES.

17:04.491 --> 17:08.361
AREN'T ALL OF GOD'S CHILDREN
SO VERY PRECIOUS?

17:08.395 --> 17:10.630
[ CHICKEN BABBLING ]

17:13.833 --> 17:15.668
CHICKEN, COME HERE.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.270
COME WITH ME.
COME HERE.

17:17.304 --> 17:19.139
COME OVER HERE.
COME ON.

17:19.172 --> 17:21.408
MAX, MAYBE YOU COULD GET HER
SOME BUBBLE WRAP OR SOMETHING?

17:21.441 --> 17:24.277
I THINK SHE NEEDS SOMETHING
TO PLAY WITH. [ CHUCKLES ]

17:24.311 --> 17:25.445
BUBBLE WRAP?

17:25.478 --> 17:27.347
Father:
WE HAVE GATHERED TODAY...

17:27.380 --> 17:28.748
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

17:28.781 --> 17:32.152
...TO WITNESS THE UNION
OF CHARMAINE AND NICK.

17:32.185 --> 17:36.689
OVER THE PAST SHORT WHILE, I
HAVE HAD THE DISTINCT PLEASURE

17:36.723 --> 17:38.858
OF GETTING TO KNOW
THIS BEAUTIFUL COUPLE

17:38.891 --> 17:41.294
AS THEY HAVE WRITTEN THEIR VOWS.

17:41.328 --> 17:42.862
I'VE ALWAYS SAID
THAT --

17:42.895 --> 17:46.366
UM, FATHER MATTHEW,
COULD YOU JUST...

17:46.399 --> 17:48.368
EVERYONE...I'M SORRY.

17:48.401 --> 17:51.738
I'M, UH...

17:51.771 --> 17:53.673
THOSE OF YOU WHO KNOW ME

17:53.706 --> 17:57.310
KNOW THAT I'VE ALWAYS TRIED
TO KEEP AN EYE OUT FOR SIGNS --

17:57.344 --> 18:01.714
SIGNS TO HELP ME
FIGURE OUT RIGHT FROM WRONG.

18:01.748 --> 18:03.450
AND, UH...

18:03.483 --> 18:05.118
AND WHEN I MET CHARMAINE,

18:05.152 --> 18:08.155
SHE WAS JUST
SUCH A BOATLOAD OF SIGNS,

18:08.188 --> 18:12.192
I THOUGHT MAYBE IT WAS JUST
THE UNIVERSE MESSING WITH ME.

18:12.225 --> 18:17.697
ANYWAY, BUT...NOW I KNOW
WHAT THOSE SIGNS MEANT.

18:17.730 --> 18:20.700
THAT...THIS MARRIAGE...

18:20.733 --> 18:22.235
DOESN'T WANT TO HAPPEN.

18:22.269 --> 18:23.603
OH, GOD.

18:23.636 --> 18:25.672
[ GUESTS MURMURING ]

18:25.705 --> 18:29.342
AND IT'S NOT
GOING TO.

18:29.376 --> 18:33.380
I'M SORRY, CHAR.

18:33.413 --> 18:36.216
LET'S GO.

18:45.892 --> 18:48.328
[ HUMMING ]

18:57.437 --> 18:58.938
IS THAT
A YELLOW CAKE?

18:58.971 --> 19:00.240
IT LOOK LIKE YELLOW.

19:00.273 --> 19:02.442
EVERYBODY LOVES
YELLOW CAKE.

19:06.646 --> 19:10.717
WAKE UP, CHAR-CHAR.

19:10.750 --> 19:13.186
I SAID WAKE UP.

19:13.220 --> 19:14.687
STOP.

19:19.226 --> 19:21.528
OW!
FUCKING CHICKEN!

19:21.561 --> 19:22.795
YOU FUCKING HURT ME!

19:22.829 --> 19:25.398
OHHH.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO.

19:25.432 --> 19:28.735
I SAID
I'D NEVER LET YOU GET HURT.

19:28.768 --> 19:32.772
I'D DO EVERYTHING...
TO...

19:32.805 --> 19:35.408
[ As Tara ]
PROTECT YOU.

19:40.447 --> 19:42.915
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED, CHAR.

19:42.949 --> 19:46.253
I DON'T.

19:46.286 --> 19:51.824
[ Voice breaking ]
BUT IT'S NOT MY FAULT.

19:51.858 --> 19:53.426
IT'S THEIRS.

19:53.460 --> 19:55.328
Bev: GIVE ME A COUPLE
OF THESE ROSES, TOO.

19:55.362 --> 19:56.996
Man:
EVERYBODY LOVES THE ROSES.

19:57.029 --> 19:58.531
WE CAN'T EAT
ALL OF THAT.

19:58.565 --> 19:59.966
FRANK, WE'LL FREEZE.

19:59.999 --> 20:03.736
WE WENT TO LAWRENCE YESTERDAY
AND MET MIMI.

20:06.005 --> 20:09.576
SHE TOLD US
SHE WAS OUR FOSTER MOTHER.

20:09.609 --> 20:12.645
WE HAD A FOSTER HOME.

20:12.679 --> 20:16.015
WE LIVED WITH HER FOR...
I DON'T KNOW HOW LONG IN 1976.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.950
I WAS 5, AND CHAR WAS 4.

20:20.387 --> 20:22.489
HOW COULD YOU
LEAVE US THERE?

20:22.522 --> 20:24.591
THAT'S ENOUGH.
MY FREEZER'S NOT THAT BIG.

20:24.624 --> 20:26.393
I'M NOT SO SURE
ABOUT THOSE DATES.

20:26.426 --> 20:28.861
GOD, MOM,
I DON'T CARE ABOUT THE DATES.

20:28.895 --> 20:31.264
WHAT I REALLY
WANT TO KNOW IS...

20:31.298 --> 20:33.366
WHY?

20:36.503 --> 20:38.905
I'LL TELL YOU WHY.

20:38.938 --> 20:42.309
OKAY. YOU AND YOUR SISTER
HAVE A HALF BROTHER.

20:42.342 --> 20:43.943
I TOLD HER.

20:43.976 --> 20:47.414
YEAH, HE TOLD ME, BUT YOU ALSO
SAID HE WAS LOSING HIS MIND.

20:47.447 --> 20:49.015
I MEAN, I NEVER KNOW
WHAT TO BELIEVE ANYMORE.

20:49.048 --> 20:51.584
OKAY, WHEN I MARRIED
YOUR FATHER, I DIDN'T KNOW...

20:51.618 --> 20:53.920
SHE DIDN'T KNOW.
...THAT HE ALREADY HAD
A SON.

20:53.953 --> 20:57.524
AND WHEN YOU WERE GIRLS,
THE BOY CAME TO LIVE WITH US.

20:57.557 --> 20:58.758
HIS NAME WAS BRYCE.

20:58.791 --> 21:00.293
THAT'S WHAT I SAID
TO YOU, CHAR.

21:00.327 --> 21:02.295
I DON'T --
[ SIGHS ]

21:02.329 --> 21:03.763
HE HAD TROUBLES.

21:03.796 --> 21:06.633
HIS MOTHER SENT HIM TO US.
HE HAD NOWHERE TO GO.

21:06.666 --> 21:08.335
HE WAS A PART OF ME.

21:08.368 --> 21:11.338
TARA, WHEN YOU TOLD ME
WHAT WAS GOING ON,

21:11.371 --> 21:14.507
I DIDN'T WANT IT
TO BE TRUE.

21:14.541 --> 21:17.477
AND THEN YOUR FATHER TOLD ME
THAT HE'D LEAVE ME

21:17.510 --> 21:19.379
IF HE HAD TO
PUT THE BOY OUT.

21:19.412 --> 21:21.848
AND I --
WELL, I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

21:21.881 --> 21:23.049
ARE YOU FUCKING KIDDING?

21:23.082 --> 21:26.419
SO I-I GOT YOU GIRLS OUT.

21:26.453 --> 21:28.421
I GOT YOU BOTH OUT
TO KEEP YOU SAFE

21:28.455 --> 21:30.056
UNTIL I FOUND A PLACE
FOR HIM.

21:30.089 --> 21:31.891
NO, NO. NO.
THIS IS NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

21:31.924 --> 21:34.894
THIS IS NOT GOOD ENOUGH!

21:34.927 --> 21:37.397
I MEAN,
YOU KNEW ALL THIS?

21:37.430 --> 21:39.966
MY WHOLE LIFE, YOU KNEW THESE
THINGS THAT COULD HAVE HELPED ME

21:39.999 --> 21:44.404
AND YOU KEPT THEM
FROM ME?!

21:44.437 --> 21:47.940
YOU SHOULD HAVE
PROTECTED ME, MOM!

21:55.582 --> 21:57.417
IS HE ALIVE?

21:57.450 --> 21:59.085
WHERE DOES HE LIVE?

21:59.118 --> 22:01.954
I'VE DATED A LOT OF FUCKING GUYS
IN THIS STATE.

22:01.988 --> 22:04.791
WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE HE IS NOW.

22:06.859 --> 22:10.763
IT'S THE PARENTS' JOB
TO PROTECT THE CHILDREN.

22:10.797 --> 22:14.667
I TRIED TO PROTECT YOU
FROM HIM.

22:14.701 --> 22:17.804
I'M SORRY.

22:17.837 --> 22:20.807
I HOPE YOU'LL BE ABLE
TO FORGIVE ME.

22:27.179 --> 22:28.715
WE'RE GONNA GO.

22:28.748 --> 22:30.717
Frank:
GET THE CAKE?

22:30.750 --> 22:33.520
Bev: YEAH. YEAH.

22:33.553 --> 22:34.921
I DON'T WANT THAT
WITH ALL THE FROSTING.

22:34.954 --> 22:36.823
I GOT THE CAKE, FRANK.
LET'S GO.

22:51.137 --> 22:53.606
I LOVE YOU, MOM.

22:53.640 --> 22:54.941
ME TOO.

23:13.860 --> 23:15.862
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

23:32.144 --> 23:33.680
HEY, CHAR.

23:33.713 --> 23:35.014
HI.

23:39.552 --> 23:43.189
SO, I, UH...

23:43.222 --> 23:46.926
HEARD YOU DIDN'T
GET MARRIED.

23:46.959 --> 23:48.227
NOPE.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.663
[ SNIFFLES ]

23:50.697 --> 23:53.866
DID MAX CALL YOU?

23:53.900 --> 23:56.202
OR DID YOU HEAR IT
FROM THE TOWN CRIER?

23:56.235 --> 23:58.004
[ LAUGHS ]

23:58.037 --> 24:00.540
UM, NO, IT WAS --

24:00.573 --> 24:02.809
IT WAS AN OLD-FASHIONED
NEWSBOY, ACTUALLY.

24:02.842 --> 24:05.077
YEAH, HE HAD
THE LITTLE CAP ON.

24:05.111 --> 24:07.680
HE SAID "XTRE"
INSTEAD OF "EXTRA."

24:07.714 --> 24:10.550
RIGHT.

24:10.583 --> 24:13.886
LOOK, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT --
WHY DON'T YOU...

24:13.920 --> 24:16.088
YOU KNOW, PUT ON
THOSE BLACK SWEATPANTS I LIKE

24:16.122 --> 24:17.824
AND LET'S GO GET A DRINK?

24:17.857 --> 24:20.960
THOSE ARE YOGA PANTS.
I DON'T WEAR SWEATPANTS.

24:20.993 --> 24:23.963
OKAY, YOGA BUTT,
PUT ON YOUR YOGA PANTS

24:23.996 --> 24:26.265
AND LET'S DOWN-DOG IT
TO THE CAT FIVE

24:26.298 --> 24:28.100
AND GET SHITTY,
ALL RIGHT?

24:28.134 --> 24:30.770
LET'S JUST
DRINK AWAY THE PAIN

24:30.803 --> 24:34.574
LIKE A COUPLE OLD FRIENDS.

24:34.607 --> 24:38.044
YOU KNOW YOU WANT TO.

24:38.077 --> 24:40.246
ACTUALLY, I DO.

24:40.279 --> 24:42.114
BUT I SHOULDN'T.

24:42.148 --> 24:45.251
OKAY, I'LL GET A DRINK,
AND THEN YOU CAN GET A...

24:45.284 --> 24:47.119
A 7UP?

24:47.153 --> 24:50.256
A 7UP -- ALL RIGHT.

24:50.289 --> 24:54.260
UM, DO -- DO YOU WANT TO...
CHANGE OUT OF THAT OR...

24:54.293 --> 24:56.996
NAH, FUCK IT.

24:57.029 --> 24:59.165
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

24:59.198 --> 25:00.600
OKAY.

25:00.633 --> 25:02.635
ALL RIGHT, YEAH.

25:02.669 --> 25:03.803
UM...

25:07.273 --> 25:12.545
YOU -- YOU JUST...
LOOK REALLY, REALLY...

25:12.579 --> 25:13.780
REALLY PRETTY.

25:13.813 --> 25:15.915
THANK YOU.

25:20.820 --> 25:25.257
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

25:25.291 --> 25:26.292
FOR WHAT?

25:26.325 --> 25:28.194
EVERYTHING.

25:31.864 --> 25:34.601
I WISH IT'D BEEN US
GETTING MARRIED TODAY.

25:34.634 --> 25:37.003
I'D STAND UP
IN FRONT OF ALL THESE PEOPLE

25:37.036 --> 25:39.271
AND I'D SAY,
"I LOVE THIS WOMAN!"

25:39.305 --> 25:40.940
[ LAUGHS ]

25:40.973 --> 25:43.342
THEN I'D LOOK IN YOUR EYES
AND I'D SAY,

25:43.375 --> 25:45.845
"IF YOU'RE TARA,
I'LL BE MAX.

25:45.878 --> 25:49.348
"BUT IF YOU'RE GIMME,
I'LL BE GOTCHA.

25:49.381 --> 25:53.653
"AND IF YOU'RE BUCK,
I'LL BE YOUR BIKE.

25:53.686 --> 25:58.124
IF YOU'RE ALICE,
I'LL BE YOUR ASTRONAUT."

26:02.161 --> 26:03.930
AND I'D CARRY CHICKEN
TO THE CAR,

26:03.963 --> 26:06.866
EVEN THOUGH I KNEW SHE WAS
PRETENDING TO BE ASLEEP.

26:12.238 --> 26:16.275
WHEN DID YOU BECOME
SO PERFECT?

26:16.308 --> 26:19.345
SINCE SHOSHANA PUT ME
ON A LOW DOSE OF PROZAC.

26:19.378 --> 26:21.580
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:23.683 --> 26:25.918
I WISH
SHE COULD PRESCRIBE.

26:28.921 --> 26:35.261
* TO BE THE MASTER OF

26:36.996 --> 26:39.298
* AND, DARLING

26:39.331 --> 26:46.773
* MY DREAMS
COULD NEVER COME TRUE *

26:46.806 --> 26:52.845
* TILL YOU GIVE ME YOUR LOVE

26:52.879 --> 27:00.286
* BUT GOOD THINGS COME
TO THOSE WHO WAIT *

27:00.319 --> 27:07.193
* AND YOU'RE
WHAT I'VE WAITED FOR *

27:07.226 --> 27:14.867
* FOR YOU ARE
ALL OF EVERYTHING *

27:14.901 --> 27:22.742
* I'LL NEED FOREVERMORE

27:22.775 --> 27:29.048
* I MUST HAVE
ALL OF EVERYTHING *

27:31.851 --> 27:39.025
* THAT'S ANY PART OF YOU

27:39.058 --> 27:45.231
* GIVE ME YOUR LIPS FOREVER

27:45.264 --> 27:50.870
* TO BE THE MASTER OF

27:53.773 --> 27:56.876
* AND, DARLING

27:56.909 --> 28:02.414
* I'LL NEED FOREVERMORE
